  "text": "Rb transport increases by ϳ40% in NPE cells exposed to ANG II. A similar stimulatory effect of ANG II on Na ϩ -K ϩ -ATPase has been reported in astrocytes (20) and kidney [CITATION_1] . In cultured NPE, the mechanism responsible for the ANG II-induced stimulation of active Na ϩ -K ϩ transport appears to involve the increase of cytoplasmic sodium concentration that occurs in ANG II-treated cells because prevention of the sodium increase abolished the stimulation of 86 Rb uptake. The ability of saralasin and losartan but not PD-123319 to suppress the sodium increase suggests that the mechanism involves activation of AT 1 receptors.",
